Our Story We did a Groupon for my other company in June and found ourselves saying "Really?!" a few too many times.  We realized that there is little to no support for merchants who use deal sites after the sale. Having read one too many stories of companies going out of business or taking huge losses from deal sites i set out to solve the problem.  I had some software built (bigboxevents.com) to take care of my own deal and now i'm making an improved version available to other merchants & deal sites.  As they say in Rework, "scratch your own itch" and "sell your bi-products" Type:  Event businesses  Who: Theaters, Sporting Events, Festivals)        * The system allows the business to manage multiple deals for the same event (or multiple events over the course of a year).     * You can not only manage your deal customers, but sell full priced tickets to increase the overall profitability on the same platform.      * It allows the users/voucher buy to view the available dates, redeem their voucher, and see updates about the specific deal from any web connected device.  Type:  Service businesses  Who: Nail Salon, Hair Salon, Spa, Mechanic)         * The system allows the business to manage multiple deals for the same schedule for both regular customers and "deal" customers on the same platform.      * It allows the users/voucher owner to view the available dates & redeem to schedule their appointment from any web connected device.      * A key feature for the merchant is they can protect their existing customer base by blocking out times that vouchers can't be redeemed. Type:  Restaurants Who: Fast food, Sit down, fine dining     * Allows the restaurant owner to process vouchers in real time by any web connected device, sms, or telephone.      * They can also implement our reservation system to incentivize their deal customers to come at off-peak hours.

Description: Fanum is a new music discovery platform that rates music Tastemakers.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: fanum.fm is a new music discovery platform that rates music Tastemakers based on how consistently and reliably they steer listeners to up-and-coming artists. They have combined elements from Yelp and Rotten Tomatoes to crowdsource fans’ musical choices and become the general public’s online guide through today’s endless sea of new music. In the past, listeners had platforms like radio and MTV to help sort through the noise and quickly get to what’s good, but they still haven’t found the new music discovery platform of tomorrow. That’s where fanum.fm steps in. fanum.fm gives everyone the opportunity to participate in the “Tastemaking” process, using a unique structure that recognizes Tastemakers for finding artists early on and utilizing their influence to build artists’ careers. Their platform rewards these dedicated fans based on how successful their artists become. They are tying a Tastemaker’s success directly to the success of the artists he or she chooses. With an unlimited number of “Likes”, “+1’s”, and “Favorites,” users of other platforms are currently not encouraged to be thoughtful about the choices they make. Although they now have access to endless amounts of new music, it’s harder than ever to distinguish quality content when it’s drowned out by all the chatter and noise. By limiting the number of artists a Tastemaker can like per month, they have presented Tastemakers' selections in a digestible form so that their online profiles can clearly communicate what they really like.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio

Full Description: Credit Re-Inventors is a Limited Liability Company, [CRI] based in Columbus, Ohio that will do business in the 9.8 billion dollar industry of credit repair. This industry continues to enjoy a 4.9% annual growth rate since 2006. What [CRI] finds so exciting is that no company has more than a 5% market share. This makes the credit repair industry prime for startup opportunities. The primary opportunity lies with over 25% of the US population having average to poor credit. Poor credit is represented by a fico score below 600. This is costing the consumer higher interest loans on housing, autos, credit card and insurance payments. Poor credit can even result in lower wages, underemployment, and total missed job opportunities. The cause of bad credit can be very complex. Real life circumstances such as divorce, loss of job, illness and death are contributing factors, however the solution is simple. [CRI] will provide over 40 years of combined credit restoration experience compiled with state of the art software we will help almost anyone reinvent and improve their credit score and rating. The result is hundreds and thousands of dollars in savings and lower interest rate loans, while giving CRI customer’s competitive edge in the employment market. The key to successful credit restoration is not only understanding the applicable laws but how they are used in the scoring model. After spending over a combined 40 years in the mortgage, finance and related industry, the principals of CRI understand and have a passion to help people reinvent themselves and improve their financial health. Years have been spent turning the consumer down for home, auto, household’s goods and other basic necessities. Now it is time for [CRI] to use their skills, knowledge, relationships and experience to Re-Invent the consumer. We believe that a Need+ a Consumer Base + Service and Experience = a Win-Win scenario rewarded by 19% margins in the first year growing.
